comments: Brunson (NYK) releases his right hand away from Reddish's (LAL) side and marginal contact occurs as Reddish's momentum continues to carry him forward during the drive.
Reddish (LAL) extends his right leg into Brunson's (NYK) path and initiates contact with Brunson's right leg, affecting Brunson's SQBR.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Reddish's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Reddish (LAL) brings his left hand up toward Randle's (NYK) upper body and marginal contact occurs as the ball falls overhead during the rebound. Reddish and Randle then make incidental foot contact with one another as they each return to the floor.
Quickley (NYK) turns alongside Reaves' (LAL) path and marginal body contact occurs as Reaves drives toward the lane.
Davis' (LAL) left arm is brought forward when marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) right side/arm after Randle secures the rebound.

Randle (NYK) turns slightly as he establishes his screening position in Reddish's (LAL) path and he does not deliver illegal contact during the pick, which occurs simultaneously with the defensive switch.
Reddish's (LAL) left arm is brought forward when marginal contact occurs with Randle's (NYK) right arm as Randle starts his drive near the free throw line.
Reddish (LAL) initiates contact with Randle's (NYK) left arm and leg after his gather, which affects his driving shot attempt.

Quickley (NYK) and Hartenstein (NYK) each bring a hand toward James' (LAL) upper body and marginal contact occurs after James' gather. Barrett (NYK) jumps vertically and legally contests James' driving shot attempt thereafter.
Reaves (LAL) engages and disengages with Barrett (NYK), and marginal contact occurs as Barrett moves to set the pick.
Reaves (LAL) moves alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) and James (LAL) both get to the loose ball simultaneously as marginal contact occurs during the tie up. A jump ball is correctly whistled.
Hartenstein (NYK) grasps and then quickly releases Davis' (LAL) jersey after the release of the jump shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) and Davis (LAL) each make contact with the ball as simultaneous incidental arm contact occurs during the rebound.
Barrett (NYK) briefly has his arm around Reaves' (LAL) midsection off-ball before correcting.
Barrett (NYK) initiates more than marginal contact across Reaves' (LAL) right arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.

Reaves (LAL) initiates contact with Brunson's (NYK) right side and affects Brunson's SQBR in transition. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Brunson (NYK) legally contests Reaves' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) and Prince (LAL) make incidental side-to-side contact with one another as they each pursue the rebound.
Prince (LAL) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before coming to a stop on the wing.
Reaves (LAL) brushes Brunson's (NYK) right arm and marginal contact occurs as Brunson starts his dribble.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the foul by Davis (LAL) on Hart (NYK) met the criteria for a clear path foul.
Reddish (LAL) makes contact with the ball and cleanly dislodges it away from Hart (NYK).
Hart (NYK) legally contests Reaves' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
